post_text:
USD 215 Parents and Families,

As a result of changes made to the National School Lunch Program we were able to extend the summer program through the end of December.

This means beginning today, ALL students will qualify for free breakfast and lunch through the end of the first semester.

While we will need to charge for any extra servings or milk beyond the lunch or breakfast, the meal itself will be free of charge.

Thank you,

USD Food Service Staff

If a student selects hybrid learning (part time on site/part time online), they must attend classes on site at least 3 days per week to participate or attend extra curricular activities/events. YOU ARE INVITED!

Baby Bronc Beginnings daycare will be having a come and go open house for the community on Friday, August 7th from 6:30pm to 8:00pm at the daycare located in the old board office building.

Please be advised that masks and social distancing will be required while attending the event.

Thank you and we look forward to seeing you there!

post_text:
As many of you have heard, yesterday the State Board of Education did not approve Governor Kelly‚Äôs Executive Order to delay the opening of schools until September 9.
The decision on when school starts now shifts to each local school board.

At this point in time we do not anticipate a change in the start day for students published on the current calendar.

A group of USD 215 staff and patrons began working to solidify our reopening guidelines. We expect those to be approved by the Board of Education at a special meeting in early August. Once they are approved by the Board we will communicate them to you directly and make sure copies are available electronically.

post_text:
Dear Lakin Community,

Today Governor Laura Kelly held a press briefing to announce Kansas Education Plans for the 2020-2021 school year. Joining her at the briefing was Dr. Lee Norman, Secretary for the Kansas Department of Health and Environment and Dr. Randy Watson, Kansas Commissioner of Education.

The briefing informed schools that on Monday, July 20, 2020, Governor Kelly will release an executive order requiring schools to delay opening until after Labor Day. It will also require daily temperature checks and masks to be worn.

We will know more on Monday after we review the exact wording of the order and will begin work on our specific reopening plan for USD 215 and will include a new academic calendar.

Dr. Martin Stessman, Superintendent of Schools
text:
Dear Lakin Community,

Today Governor Laura Kelly held a press briefing to announce Kansas Education Plans for the 2020-2021 school year. Joining her at the briefing was Dr. Lee Norman, Secretary for the Kansas Department of Health and Environment and Dr. Randy Watson, Kansas Commissioner of Education.

The briefing informed schools that on Monday, July 20, 2020, Governor Kelly will release an executive order requiring schools to delay opening until after Labor Day. It will also require daily temperature checks and masks to be worn.

We will know more on Monday after we review the exact wording of the order and will begin work on our specific reopening plan for USD 215 and will include a new academic calendar.

Dr. Martin Stessman, Superintendent of Schools

post_text:
ATTENTION: 2017, 2018, and 2019 Hutton, Beymer, Krehbiel, and Henderson Scholarship Recipients!!

REMINDER: The funds for these scholarships have been turned over to the Kearny County Community Foundation. The school will no longer be writing the checks for these 4 scholarships. The KCCF will be issuing these checks but the checks will now be sent directly to your college of attendance.

You will still need to submit your spring grade card or transcript (official or unofficial) to the LHS Office. Be sure whatever you submit shows your total hours taken this past year and your cumulative GPA. In addition, you will need to indicate what college you will be attending and give Kay or Roelfina your social security number. All this information will then be forwarded to the KCCF.

There is also a deadline - all this information needs to be submitted to the LHS office by no later than August 10, 2020.

A note that gave all this information was sent to you in January with your spring semester check.

If you have any questions, please contact kim Lohman at kim.lohman@usd215.org

ATTENTION!!!
All past, current, or future LB Baseball Players. There will be an Open BP (batting practice) on the following Sunday evenings, in the cages, out at Louck's Park, starting at 6 pm. June 14 and 28, July 12 and 26. Dates are subject to change, but the first Sunday is set. Coach Davidson, Coach Beitz, and some Alumni will be there to throw you some pitches.
